 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Etadanik Mistmorgue</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> The holgresh elder beads I would consider a legendary item, but not because it cannot be replaced (stalking probes replace it fine).  Rather, I would consider it legendary because it gives a class an ability they never had before AND no longer drops.  *ANY* item that is still available is not legendary, because to be legendary means the item is unique, and being unique there must only be a limited amount of such an item, without new ones entering the economy and eventually becoming available to a wide-spread number of people.  The pre-nerf fungi staff (because its regen is so high), the CoS, the pre-nerf guise of the deceiver, etc. are all such items.  +HP, +regen, +FT items are not in this category, because all they do is make you a bit more efficient, while the items I mentioned above allows you to do things other people, without those items, simply are not capable of doing.</P><P>Now as for the usefulness of the beads, I will tell you this: on any uber mob that is immune to magic or immune to disease, the beads will shine.  However, they are easily replaceable in such situations by stalking probes or by asking a mage to summon you some.  Where the beads cannot be replaced is while soloing and scouting.  Admittedly, they were more useful back then when you could pull with them, but there is a certain advantage to being able to explore anywhere you want, without fear of aggro, as well...</P><P><BR>Etadanik the Redeemed</font></td>
